<seg id="10">I would say to people, “America is the only country I have ever lived in whose diversity was so welcoming that you can be exactly who you are and easily find acceptance in a community of like-minded people.” </seg>
<seg id="11">I even penned a love letter, waxing lyrical about her greatness. </seg>
<seg id="12">Then Donald Trump happened. </seg>
<seg id="13">Much has been written about the man’s xenophobia and racism. </seg>
<seg id="14">To me, the most extraordinary aspect of his rise is how easily he wears his bigotry. </seg>
<seg id="15">He doesn’t dog-whistle, to borrow a turn of phrase. </seg>
