<seg id="1916">The Sebastiao family (with their girl, Merrui, sporting a with the yogurt mustache) stand with Concepción González Ramírez, also known as Mama Africa. </seg>
<seg id="1917">The Sebastiaos came from Angola via Brazil, and they hope to reach Boston. </seg>
<seg id="1918">Credit: Amy Bracken </seg>
<seg id="1919">“Yes, yes,” he says, with a laugh. “I feel she is really like that, because African women are very nice women. </seg>
