<seg id="1939">He started helping them get a fair deal, and offered up his home for a buck a night. </seg>
<seg id="1940">Now, up to 25 people, mostly Haitian, are staying here. </seg>
<seg id="1941">Some sleep on quilts on the floor, but there’s electricity, laundry, and an outdoor cooking area. </seg>
<seg id="1942">Valenzuela says he knows what his guests go through. </seg>
