<seg id="2766">In the same video, one of the paper's reporters says that according to the Public Safety Institute of Rio de Janeiro, there are 843 areas in the city that are under the control of criminal organizations. </seg>
<seg id="2767">The editorial also says: </seg>
<seg id="2768">We are aware that a war discourse, when distorted, can be used to cover up truculent acts by a police force that shoots first, asks later. </seg>
